Second Lady Karen Pence, in partnership with American Corporate Partners, hosted a meeting with 46 businesses in Washington, DC to discuss military spouse employment solutions. Kellyanne Conway, Counselor to the President, delivered brief remarks and introduced Mrs. Pence. Mrs. Pence emphasized the importance of hiring and retaining military spouses and encouraged businesses to collaborate with the Department of Defense's Military Spouse Employment Partnership. The meeting participants then divided into small working groups to discuss potential solutions to military spouse employment challenges. American Corporate Partners developed a mentorship program for military spouses to help with career development, networking, and professional skills building.